  <h1 class="mb-6">Architecture: GreenScape Landscaping</h1>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>What is an architecture document?</strong> The architecture defines <em>how to build it</em> technically. It takes the PRD (what to build) and the design spec (how it looks) and turns them into a technical plan: what technologies to use, how to structure the code, how data flows through the system, and how the pieces connect. In later projects, this will include database schemas, API contracts, and complex component relationships. For GreenScape, the architecture is simple — but the artefact exists. In later projects, you'll direct AI to generate the architecture, and your job will be reviewing it for over-engineering and missing dependencies.</p>
